# File Hub AI Assistant Directives

## Code Style & Standards
- Follow idiomatic Go conventions (gofmt, godoc)
- Use Go modules for dependency management
- Prefer clear, readable code over clever optimizations
- Follow project-specific coding standards in CONTRIBUTING.md

## Contribution Guidelines
- Focus on core functionality: file synchronization and storage for personal use
- Use standard Go libraries where possible
- Optimize for readability and maintainability
- Prioritize Linux-specific optimizations and features

## Code Review Instructions
- Check for proper error handling (multi-value returns, wrapping)
- Identify goroutine leak risks and channel misuse
- Suggest improvements for concurrency patterns
- Verify proper file handling with os/io packages

## Documentation Requirements
- Maintain API documentation with Godoc
- Explain synchronization algorithms clearly
- Document performance considerations
- Keep configuration documentation current

## Error Handling
- Emphasize proper error wrapping and handling
- Suggest appropriate logging with structured logging
- Identify edge cases in network operations
- Review deferred cleanup patterns
